+# Wine Stock Report Generator
+
+A command-line tool that converts a warehouse stock-on-hand CSV file into a human-readable Markdown report, with 9-litre-equivalent calculations, grouping by variety/vintage/market, low-stock warnings, and data quality validation.
+
+## Features
+
+- **CSV Import**: Load warehouse stock data with automatic data cleaning and validation
+- **Wine Metadata Parsing**: Extract vintage, variety, market, bottle size, and pack size from descriptions
+- **9LE Calculations**: Convert stock quantities to 9-litre-equivalent cases using Decimal arithmetic
+- **Flexible Grouping**: Generate summary tables grouped by variety, vintage, market, pack size, lot, or none
+- **Stock Basis Selection**: Choose between OnHand or Available stock for totals
+- **Low-Stock Warnings**: Automatically identify items below a configurable threshold
+- **Dry Goods Support**: Separate handling for non-wine items with original unit reporting
+- **Data Warnings**: Comprehensive validation warnings for data quality issues
+- **Interactive & Non-Interactive Modes**: Interactive prompts or command-line flags for CI/automation
+
+## Installation
+
+No installation required. The tool uses Python 3.11+ standard library only.
+
+## Usage
+
+### Non-Interactive Mode (Recommended for CI/Scripts)
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv --no-interactive
+```
+
+This generates `stock-report.md` using all default options.
+
+### Interactive Mode (Default)
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv
+```
+
+The tool will prompt you for six configuration options:
+
+1. **Stock Basis** (OnHand or Available) - default: Available
+2. **Include Dry Goods** (yes/no) - default: yes
+3. **Grouping** (variety, vintage, market, pack_size, lot, or none) - default: variety
+4. **Low-Stock Warnings** (yes/no) - default: yes
+5. **Low-Stock Threshold** (in 9LE) - default: 10
+6. **Output Filename** - default: stock-report.md
+
+Press Enter to accept defaults; type your choice and press Enter to override.
+
+### Command-Line Options
+
+All command-line flags can be used with `--no-interactive` for full automation:
+
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter examples/stock_sample.csv \
+  --basis OnHand \
+  --group-by vintage \
+  --no-dry-goods \
+  --no-low-stock-warnings \
+  --low-stock-threshold 5 \
+  --output my-report.md \
+  --no-interactive
+```
+
+#### Flag Reference
+
+- `--basis {OnHand,Available}` - Use OnHand or Available quantities for wine totals (default: Available)
+- `--group-by {variety,vintage,market,pack_size,lot,none}` - Primary summary grouping (default: variety)
+- `--include-dry-goods` / `--no-dry-goods` - Include or exclude dry goods section (default: include)
+- `--low-stock-warnings` / `--no-low-stock-warnings` - Show or hide low-stock warnings (default: show)
+- `--low-stock-threshold N` - Threshold in 9LE for low-stock alerts, accepts decimals (default: 10)
+- `--output PATH` - Output markdown filename (default: stock-report.md)
+- `--no-interactive` - Skip all interactive prompts and use effective option values
+
+## Report Structure
+
+The generated Markdown report includes:
+
+### Header
+- Generation timestamp
+- Source CSV filename
+- Warehouse(s) in data
+- Stock basis used
+
+### Executive Summary
+- Row counts by type
+- Total wine stock in 9LE
+- Available, allocated, and pending cases totals
+- Lowest stock item
+- Data warning count
+
+### Stock Summary by Grouping
+Tables showing:
+- Selected grouping field (Variety, Vintage, Market, Pack Size, or Lot)
+- Row count
+- Cases quantity
+- 9LE equivalent
+
+### Detailed Finished Goods Table
+All wine stock rows with:
+- Item ID
+- Description
+- Lot code
+- Available quantity
+- Units (Cases/Eaches)
+- 9LE (or `—` if pack size cannot be parsed)
+
+### Low-Stock Warnings (if enabled)
+Items below the configured threshold, listed with their 9LE quantity.
+
+### Dry Goods Summary (if included)
+- Item ID
+- Description
+- Available quantity
+- Units (usually Eaches)
+
+### Data Warnings
+Non-fatal validation issues:
+- Unknown variety codes
+- Unparseable bottle/pack sizes
+- Negative stock values
+- Available > OnHand mismatches
+- Material balance errors (OnHand - Allocated - Pending ≠ Available)
+- Non-numeric values
+
+## Data Cleaning & Validation
+
+The tool automatically:
+
+- Parses decimal numbers and thousands separators (e.g., "2,216.50" → 2216.50)
+- Handles blank nullable numeric fields (treats as 0)
+- Warns on negative values without crashing
+- Tolerates unparseable descriptions and marks fields as Unknown
+- Validates required CSV columns (Type1, Item, Description, OnHand, Warehouse, Allocated, Pending, Available, Units)
+- Checks for data consistency issues and reports them as warnings
+
+## 9LE Calculation
+
+Stock is converted to 9-litre equivalents using:
+
+```
+9LE = (quantity × pack_size × bottle_size_ml) / 9000
+```
+
+Examples:
+- 48.58 cases of 750ml/12p = 48.58 9LE (one 12-pack = 9 litres)
+- 26.67 cases of 750ml/6p = 13.34 9LE (one 6-pack = 4.5 litres)
+
+## Variety Code Mapping
+
+Recognized variety codes:
+
+| Code | Variety |
+|---|---|
+| CHR | Chardonnay |
+| SAB | Sauvignon Blanc |
+| PIN | Pinot Noir |
+| PIG | Pinot Gris |
+| PRO | Rosé |
+| RDB | Red Blend |
+| MXD | Mixed / Consolidated |
+
+Unknown codes remain visible in the report with a data warning.
+
+## Running Tests
+
+```bash
+python3 -m unittest discover -s tests
+```
+
+Tests cover:
+- CSV loading with various numeric formats
+- Wine description parsing
+- 9LE calculations
+- Grouping and aggregation
+- Validation warnings
+- Report generation
+- End-to-end acceptance examples
+
+## Exit Codes
+
+- `0` - Success
+- `1` - Data error (missing file, missing column, unreadable CSV)
+- `2` - Usage error (unknown flag, missing argument)
+
+## Example Commands
+
+### Standard report with defaults
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --no-interactive
+```
+
+### Report by vintage with custom threshold
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv \
+  --group-by vintage \
+  --low-stock-threshold 5 \
+  --no-interactive
+```
+
+### OnHand basis without dry goods
+```bash
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv \
+  --basis OnHand \
+  --no-dry-goods \
+  --output onhand-report.md \
+  --no-interactive
+```
+
+### All grouping options
+```bash
+# By variety (default)
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --group-by variety --no-interactive
+
+# By vintage
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --group-by vintage --no-interactive
+
+# By market
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --group-by market --no-interactive
+
+# By pack size
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --group-by pack_size --no-interactive
+
+# By lot
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --group-by lot --no-interactive
+
+# No grouping (just executive summary and details)
+python3 -m wine_stock_reporter stock.csv --group-by none --no-interactive
+```
+
+## Project Structure
+
+```
+wine_stock_reporter/
+  __init__.py
+  __main__.py
+  cli.py              # Command-line interface and interactive prompts
+  csv_loader.py       # CSV parsing and data cleaning
+  models.py           # Data structures (StockRow, ValidationWarning, etc.)
+  parser.py           # Wine description parsing
+  calculations.py     # 9LE and aggregation logic
+  validation.py       # Data validation and warnings
+  report.py           # Markdown report generation
+tests/
+  __init__.py
+  test_csv_loader.py
+  test_parser.py
+  test_calculations.py
+  test_validation.py
+  test_report.py
+examples/
+  stock_sample.csv    # Sample warehouse data
+README.md
+PRD.md
+GOAL.md
+```
+
+## Requirements
+
+- Python 3.11 or later
+- Standard library only (csv, decimal, argparse, datetime, pathlib, collections)
+
+## License
+
+Internal use only.
